<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1192,1644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,326,1386,1412]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is characterized by the forewing ground color ochreous yellow, white along the distal 
<number box="[229,244,1425,1451]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="5.0">5</number>
/ 
<number box="[254,270,1425,1451]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="6.0">6</number>
of the costal margin, yellowish white from below the fold to the dorsal margin, and with a longitudinal white line along the upper margin of the cell (
<figureCitation box="[830,900,1464,1490]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1452,1476]" captionTargetBox="[254,1315,293,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,293,1446]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pyroderces sarcogypsa (Meyrick). a, adult; b, male genitalia (gen. slide No. ZZW 07339); c, female genitalia (gen. slide No. ZZW 07338)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190979/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[884,900,1464,1490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a). It is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1104,1429,1464,1489]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Pyroderces" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrogrammos">
<emphasis box="[1104,1429,1464,1489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Pyroderces argyrogrammos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the male valvae with setose basal lobes (
<figureCitation box="[957,1029,1502,1528]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1452,1476]" captionTargetBox="[254,1315,293,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,293,1446]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pyroderces sarcogypsa (Meyrick). a, adult; b, male genitalia (gen. slide No. ZZW 07339); c, female genitalia (gen. slide No. ZZW 07338)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190979/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1013,1029,1502,1528]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b), and the female signa consisting of paired rows of densely compact spines of similar shape and size (
<figureCitation box="[948,1020,1541,1567]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1452,1476]" captionTargetBox="[254,1315,293,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,293,1446]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pyroderces sarcogypsa (Meyrick). a, adult; b, male genitalia (gen. slide No. ZZW 07339); c, female genitalia (gen. slide No. ZZW 07338)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190979/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1003,1020,1541,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
